com.jayway.android.robotium.remotecontrol.solo

Class SoloWorker

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jayway.android.robotium.remotecontrol.solo.SoloWorker
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DebugListener, NamedListener
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Solo

    public class SoloWorker
extends java.lang.Object
implements DebugListener
    Normally, this class would not be used directly. Use the Solo class, instead. Default abstract usage: 

     SoloWorker solo = new SoloWorker();
 solo.setLogsInterface(alog);
 solo.initialize();
 (use the API)
 solo.shutdown();
    Since:

    (LeiWang) Mar 09, 2012 Add methods to turn on/off debug log of protocol/runner. Add method to shutdown remote service on device.
    (LeiWang) Mar 09, 2012 Move static method parseStringArrayList() to Message class.
    See Also:
    Solo

      • initialize

        public void initialize()
                throws RemoteException,
                       java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException,
                       ShutdownInvocationException
        Called to initialize RemoteControl communications with a remote client and get it to the Ready state. However, the routine only performs this initialization if it is instancing a new remote controller. If the remote controller already exists, then we must assume initialization of that remote control object has opened or will happen elsewhere since it was not instanced by this class. Initial default implementation performs: 

         control = createRemoteControll();
 control.addListener(this);
 control.setLogsInterface(log);
 control.start();
 control.waitForRemoteConnected(default_connect_stimeout);
 control.waitForRemoteReady(default_ready_stimeout);
        Throws:
        RemoteException - -- if there is a problem with RemoteControl initialization.
        java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException - -- if the initialization and remote connection does not complete in timeout period.
        ShutdownInvocationException - -- if the remote client unexpectedly performs a shutdown.
        See Also:
        setRemoteControl(SoloRemoteControl, boolean), SoloRemoteControl.waitForRemoteReady(int), SoloRemoteControl.setLogsInterface(LogsInterface)

      • processFailure

        public void processFailure(java.lang.String action,
                  java.lang.String message)
        Handle the reporting or logging of action or test failures.

        This is enabled by default. Callers can override default failure processing by setting doProcessFailure = false.

        This implementation uses the LogsInterface that should be provided at or immediately following the creation of the Class instance. Subclasses may wish to use true jUnit reporting or other mechanisms.

        If the LogsInterface call throws an Exception for any reason--including a NullPointerException because it was never provided or initialized--the implementation will log to our err PrintStream with the following format: cause +": "+ message

        Parameters:
        cause - -- Normally, the action or id of the call that generated the failure.
        message - -- The failure message provided for that action or id. If the message is null the implementation will use FAIL_SUFFIX.
        See Also:
        LogsInterface.fail(String, String), FAIL_SUFFIX

      • processSuccess

        public void processSuccess(java.lang.String action,
                  java.lang.String message)
        Handle the reporting or logging of action or test success.

        This is enabled by default. A truer jUnit experience can be achieved by setting doHandleSuccess = false.

        This implementation uses the LogsInterface that should be provided at or immediately following the creation of the Class instance. Subclasses may wish to use true jUnit reporting or other mechanisms.

        If the LogsInterface call throws an Exception for any reason--including a NullPointerException because it was never provided or initialized--the implementation will log to our out PrintStream with the following format: cause +": "+ message

        Parameters:
        cause - -- Normally, the action or id of the call that generated the success.
        message - -- The success message provided for that action or id, if any. This can be null. If the message is null this implementation will use PASS_SUFFIX.
        See Also:
        #doHandleSuccess, LogsInterface.pass(String, String), PASS_SUFFIX

      • shutdown

        public void shutdown()
        Initial default implementation performs: 

         control.shutdown();
 This will stop the SoloRemoteControlRunner on the computer side.
        Note: If you want to stop the remote service on the device side,
        you should call shutdownRemote(), and you MUST call it before
        calling this shutdown() method.
        See Also:
        SoloRemoteControl.shutdown(), shutdownRemote()

      • shutdownRemote

        public boolean shutdownRemote()
        Initial default implementation performs: 

         control.performRemoteShutdown(int,int,int);
        Note: This method will stop the remote service on the device side,
        you MUST call it before calling shutdown() method.
        See Also:
        SoloRemoteControl.performRemoteShutdown(int, int, int), shutdown()
